We are currently taking part in the EU project on P alpable Computing that aims at providing a new perspecti ve on ambient computing [palcom2004]. One k ey issue in this project is that it must be possible for users to construct ne w systems from e xisting components, and for deconstructing e xisting systems into their constituents. In this position paper we present some ideas we ha v about using domain-specifi languages for programming such palpable systems.